Caragana korshinskii

   [4186.jpg]
    Authority
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4186

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A spreading thorny shrub reaching a height of up to 2.5 m.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Long-lived perennial, reaching an age of 40-75 years.
   COMMON NAMES
   Caragana korshinskii.
   FURTHER INF
   Caragana korshinskii can be found in the sandy deserts, on steep slopes
   and undulating plains of Inner Mongolia, China. It forms nitogen-fixing
   modules. It is resistant to heat, cold drought, wind erosion, sand
   burial and hail storms. Under good conditions the fodder yield may be
   up to 560 kg/ha. (pH estimated by the compiler).

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Walls J 1982 pp 69 [USE, TEMP, TEXT, RAIN]
   Shing T 1992 pp 309 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, FER, DEP]

